<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-26-0152 </DOCNO><TEXT>The endeavours to achieve a cooperation on a broad basis between OPECand non-OPEC countries have come to nothing for the time being. To besure, demand for OPEC oil will go up in the second half of 1988, yetthe average production of the suppliers of the cartel will hardly runto more than 60 percent of their capacity. The collapse of prices canbe avoided only if the oil ministers, at their meeting on June 8, succeedin concluding a new agreement laying down quotas.</TEXT></DOC>